allows you to set aside a portion of your before tax pay to reimburse eligible dependent day care expenses eligible expenses include childcare up to age 13 the date the child turns age 13 expenses occurring after a child's 13th birthday are not eligible you can also use this account to care for a disabled dependent adult child care subsidy grant to help stanford faculty and staff meet child care expenses the child care subsidy grant ccsg program administered by stanford's worklife office provides up to $5000 a year in tax free grants for eligible child care expenses grant amounts are based on the information in your application for more information go to the worklife home page or call the worklife office at 650 723 2660 important restrictions fsas have some restrictions on allowable expenses and any money left in your account at the end of the year will be forfeited be sure to read more about these plans and carefully calculate your contribution before enrolling quick links your fsa tool kit learn more about flexible spending accounts resources flexible spending account fsa faq your fsa when employment ends health care fsa claim form dependent day care fsa claim form fsa user guide contacts stanford benefits tel 877 905 2985 option 9 home benefits overview medical & life retirement resource library contacts mybenefits site map how to use this site human resources stanford university stanford university terms of use copyright complaints document download
